quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  40,26,"And said Firaun, “Allow me to kill Moosa and let him pray to his Lord; I fear that he will change your religion or cause chaos in the land!”"
  40,27,"Said Moosa, “I seek the refuge of mine and your Lord, from every haughty person who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning.”"
  40,28,"And said a Muslim man from the people of Firaun, who used to hide his faith, “What! You want to kill a man just because he says, ‘Allah is my Lord’ whereas he has indeed brought clear signs to you from your Lord? And supposedly if he is speaking wrongly, then the calamity of wrongful speech is upon him; and if he is truthful, then part of what he promises you will reach you; indeed Allah does not guide any transgressor, excessive liar.”"
  40,29,"“O my people! You now rule the earth, dominant; so who will save us from Allah’s punishment if it comes upon us?” Said Firaun, “I only explain to you what I think is correct, and I show you only the right path.”"
  40,30,"And the believer said, “O my people! I fear for you a day similar to that of the earlier groups!”"
  40,31,"“Like the tradition of the people of Nooh, and Aad, and Thamud and others after them; and Allah does not will injustice upon bondmen.”"
  40,32,"“O my people! I fear for you a day on which will be a great outcry!”"
  40,33,"“A day when you will turn back fleeing; none can save you from Allah; and whomever Allah sends astray, there is no guide for him.”"
